const projects = [
  {
    id: 1,
    title: 'Blink',
    vid: './image/blink.png',
    info: "Blink, similar to Simon, tests a users ability to follow the pattern as a tile lights up in a random order.",
    technologies: ['Vanilla JS', 'CSS', 'Backend: Ruby on Rails'],
    github: 'https://github.com/christine1226/mod3_project'
  },
  {
    id: 2,
    title: 'Sea Learner',
    vid: 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/y-aZkFSJ6pU',
    info: "Learning App targeted for preschoolers. A user develops the ability to type, correctly pronounce words, and become familiar with colors, shapes, etc. Progress is kept track of in a parent portal, where a parent will be able to see the amount of correct and incorrect answers.",
    technologies: ['Redux', 'React', 'CSS', 'Semantic UI', 'Speech Recognition Webkit', 'Speech Synthesis Webkit', 'Backend: Ruby on Rails'],
    github: 'https://github.com/christine1226/SeaCards'
  },
  {
    id: 3,
    title: 'NYC Event Manager (Lituation)',
    vid: 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/C_GogFbJeCc',
    info: "Ruby on Rails frontend and backend. This project was created for user to be able to create an account and post events they are aware of and also view other created events. Events are sorted by date, time and categories.",
    technologies: ['Ruby', 'CSS', 'Backend: Ruby on Rails'],
    github: 'https://github.com/christine1226/lituation'
  },
  {
    id: 4,
    title: 'Boozer',
    vid: './image/blink.png',
    info: "Boozer is an app used to display drink recipes. Boozer incorporates a dynamic form to share new drink recipes.",
    technologies: ['React', 'CSS', 'Semantic UI', 'Backend: Ruby on Rails'],
    github: 'https://github.com/christine1226/boozer-react'
  }
]

export default projects
